{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778524018123,"sessionID":"ses_1e7bd2da3ffezVJth0t7vFehuj","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"chatcmpl-tool-98db0fb751bb470b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_0002422.obo"},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/terms/UBERON_0002422.obo</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: [Term]\n2: id: UBERON:0002422\n3: name: fourth ventricle\n4: def: \"Part of the ventricular system of the brain, forming a single large irregularly shaped cavity located on the midline of the rhombencephalon, between the medulla, pons and the isthmus ventrally and the cerebellum dorsally. It is continuous with the cerebral aqueduct anteriorally and the central canal of the spinal cord posteriorly. It communicates with the subarachnoid space through its lateral and median apertures.\" [BIRNLEX:1256]\n5: subset: pheno_slim\n6: subset: uberon_slim\n7: subset: vertebrate_core\n8: synonym: \"4th ventricle\" RELATED [MA:0000196]\n9: synonym: \"fourth ventricle proper\" RELATED [BAMS:V4]\n10: synonym: \"hindbrain ventricle\" RELATED NON_MAMMAL [VHOG:0000006]\n11: synonym: \"IVth ventricle\" RELATED [VHOG:0000006]\n12: synonym: \"rhombencephalic ventricle\" RELATED [VHOG:0000006]\n13: synonym: \"rhombencephalic vesicle\" NARROW [ZFA:0000110]\n14: synonym: \"ventricle IV\" EXACT [ZFA:0000110]\n15: synonym: \"ventricle of hindbrain\" RELATED NON_MAMMAL [BTO:0003426]\n16: synonym: \"ventricle of rhombencephalon\" RELATED [BTO:0003426]\n17: synonym: \"ventriculus quartus\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Fourth_ventricle]\n18: xref: AAO:0011043\n19: xref: BAMS:4V\n20: xref: BAMS:V4\n21: xref: BIRNLEX:1256\n22: xref: BM:Pons-4V\n23: xref: BTO:0003426\n24: xref: CALOHA:TS-2015\n25: xref: DHBA:10669\n26: xref: DHBA:12805\n27: xref: DMBA:126651782\n28: xref: EHDAA2:0000100\n29: xref: EHDAA:896\n30: xref: EMAPA:16917\n31: xref: EV:0100310\n32: xref: FMA:78469\n33: xref: GAID:610\n34: xref: HBA:9421\n35: xref: MA:0000196\n36: xref: MBA:145\n37: xref: MESH:D020546\n38: xref: NCIT:C12828\n39: xref: neuronames:621\n40: xref: SCTID:180932000\n41: xref: TAO:0000110\n42: xref: UMLS:C0149556 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Fourth_Ventricle_of_the_Brain\"}\n43: xref: VHOG:0000006\n44: xref: Wikipedia:Fourth_ventricle\n45: xref: XAO:0003099\n46: xref: ZFA:0000110\n47: intersection_of: UBERON:0004086 ! brain ventricle\n48: intersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002028 ! hindbrain\n49: relationship: contributes_to_morphology_of UBERON:0002028 ! hindbrain\n50: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0013149 {source=\"EHDAA2\"} ! hindbrain vesicle\n51: property_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7d/Gray734.png\" xsd:anyURI\n52: property_value: external_definition \"Fluid-filled brain cavity. Kimmel et al, 1995.[TAO]\" xsd:string {date_retrieved=\"2012-08-14\", external_class=\"TAO:0000110\", ontology=\"TAO\", source=\"ZFIN:curator\"}\n53: property_value: external_definition \"Irregularly shaped cavity in the rhombencephalon, between the medulla oblongata, the pons, and the isthmus in front, and the cerebellum behind. It is continuous with the central canal of the cord below and with the cerebral aqueduct above, and through its lateral and median apertures it communicates with the subarachnoid space.[AAO]\" xsd:string {date_retrieved=\"2012-06-20\", external_class=\"AAO:0011043\", ontology=\"AAO\", source=\"UBERON:0002422\"}\n54: property_value: external_definition \"The fourth ventricle is an irregularly shaped cavity in the rhombencephalon, between the medulla oblongata, the pons, and the isthmus in front, and the cerebellum behind. It is continuous with the central canal of the cord below and with the cerebral aqueduct above, and through its lateral and median apertures it communicates with the subarachnoid space[GO][GO:0021592].\" xsd:string {source=\"GO:0021592\"}\n55: property_value: homology_notes \"The early development of most vertebrate brains is similar (...). The zebrafish neural tube follows the same basic differentiation pattern as the mammalian neural tube (reference 1); The brain develops from three embryonic enlargements of the neural tube, which later differentiate into five regions. A forebrain differentiates into telencephalon and diencephalon. The midbrain, or mesencephalon, remains undivided. The hindbrain divides into the metencephalon and myelencephalon. Cavities within the brain enlarge to form a series of interconnected ventricles (reference 2).[well established][VHOG]\" xsd:string {date_retrieved=\"2012-09-17\", external_class=\"VHOG:0000006\", ontology=\"VHOG\", source=\"ISBN:978-0878932504 Gilbert SF, Developmental Biology (2006) p.381-382, ISBN:978-0030223693 Liem KF, Bemis WE, Walker WF, Grande L, Functional Anatomy of the Vertebrates: An Evolutionary Perspective (2001) p.500\", source=\"http://bgee.unil.ch/\"}\n56: \n\n(End of file - total 56 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"[Term]\nid: UBERON:0002422\nname: fourth ventricle\ndef: \"Part of the ventricular system of the brain, forming a single large irregularly shaped cavity located on the midline of the rhombencephalon, between the medulla, pons and the isthmus ventrally and the cerebellum dorsally. It is continuous with the cerebral aqueduct anteriorally and the central canal of the spinal cord posteriorly. It communicates with the subarachnoid space through its lateral and median apertures.\" [BIRNLEX:1256]\nsubset: pheno_slim\nsubset: uberon_slim\nsubset: vertebrate_core\nsynonym: \"4th ventricle\" RELATED [MA:0000196]\nsynonym: \"fourth ventricle proper\" RELATED [BAMS:V4]\nsynonym: \"hindbrain ventricle\" RELATED NON_MAMMAL [VHOG:0000006]\nsynonym: \"IVth ventricle\" RELATED [VHOG:0000006]\nsynonym: \"rhombencephalic ventricle\" RELATED [VHOG:0000006]\nsynonym: \"rhombencephalic vesicle\" NARROW [ZFA:0000110]\nsynonym: \"ventricle IV\" EXACT [ZFA:0000110]\nsynonym: \"ventricle of hindbrain\" RELATED NON_MAMMAL [BTO:0003426]\nsynonym: \"ventricle of rhombencephalon\" RELATED [BTO:0003426]\nsynonym: \"ventriculus quartus\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Fourth_ventricle]\nxref: AAO:0011043\nxref: BAMS:4V\nxref: BAMS:V4","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"terms/UBERON_0002422.obo","time":{"start":1778524018114,"end":1778524018122}},"id":"prt_e18495651001FUkw7TrrCSMjr3","sessionID":"ses_1e7bd2da3ffezVJth0t7vFehuj","messageID":"msg_e1848646200135SR7Ijt517hvG"}}
